<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include('partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/nav') %>
    <main>
      <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="container narrow">
          <p class="eyebrow">About TAIG</p>
          <h1>Who we are</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            TAIG stands for <strong>The AI Guy</strong> — a technology services practice built on
            one belief: the best solutions come from understanding the business first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container narrow">
          <h2>What TAIG stands for</h2>
          <p>
            The AI Guy represents a straightforward promise — expert technology guidance delivered
            with clarity and honesty. We work with business owners, operators, and teams who need
            a trusted partner to navigate IT challenges, evaluate options, and implement change
            that actually sticks.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our name reflects accessibility. Technology doesn't have to be intimidating or opaque.
            We translate complex situations into clear choices so you can move forward with confidence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container narrow">
          <h2>Business philosophy</h2>
          <p>
            We believe technology is a means, not an end. Every tool, platform, or process should
            serve a business purpose — reducing friction, improving reliability, or enabling growth.
            When technology drifts from that purpose, it becomes cost without return.
          </p>
          <p>
            TAIG operates as an extension of your team: pragmatic, responsive, and focused on what
            matters to your operation today while keeping an eye on where you're headed tomorrow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 class="section-title">How we work</h2>
          <div class="card-grid card-grid-2">
            <article class="card card-feature">
              <h3>Start With The Problem</h3>
              <p>
                Before we discuss tools, budgets, or timelines, we invest time understanding what's
                actually going wrong — or what opportunity you're trying to capture. Symptoms get
                documented. Root causes get explored. Only then do solutions enter the conversation.
              </p>
              <p>
                This principle protects you from expensive missteps and ensures recommendations
                address the real issue, not just the loudest complaint.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="card card-feature">
              <h3>Technology as a Business Enabler</h3>
              <p>
                We evaluate technology through a business lens: Does it save time? Reduce risk?
                Improve customer experience? Support your people? If the answer isn't clear, we
                say so — even when that means recommending less, not more.
              </p>
              <p>
                Our role is to connect operational reality with technical capability so your
                organization gains leverage, not dependency.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="nebula" class="section section-alt nebula-section">
        <div class="container narrow">
          <p class="eyebrow">Nebula</p>
          <h2>Seeing the whole picture</h2>
          <p>
            Nebula is TAIG's structured approach to understanding your organization before
            making recommendations. It guides conversations across people, processes, and
            systems so nothing important gets overlooked.
          </p>
          <p>
            For visitors and clients alike, Nebula means this: we won't hand you a generic
            answer. We take the time to learn how your business runs, where the pressure
            points are, and what success looks like for you — then we build a path that fits.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section cta-band">
        <div class="container cta-band-inner">
          <h2>Want to learn how we can help?</h2>
          <p>Explore our services or reach out for a conversation.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="/services" class="btn btn-primary">View Services</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Contact Us</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
